equation_narrative.headline: Buried hydrophobic core context drives confident isoleucine prediction through structural contacts
equation_narrative.story: Position 44 in ubiquitin sits in a deeply buried hydrophobic environment, surrounded by 8 structural contacts predominantly carrying aliphatic chemistry. Through layers 1-23, the model assembles this context through structural attention, with the representation consistently projecting toward hydrophobic residues (V, L, A) in the logit lens. The perception-to-decision transition occurs sharply at L24-26, where isoleucine-specific prediction channels activate. By L29, I dominates at 68%, rising to 99% by L33 as MLP neurons in the final layers cast decisive votes for the branched aliphatic structure that best fits the assembled hydrophobic core context.

perception_phase.summary: Layers 1-23 assemble a strongly hydrophobic structural context. Eight structural contacts within the local environment are read through attention heads at L29 (heads 18 and 7 write +3.3 and +2.9 toward I, with 0.93 and 0.88 structural attention respectively). Nine co-evolving positions provide additional constraint, though structural information dominates. The logit lens shows the representation character shifting among hydrophobic residues: A leads early (20% at L0), then V and L compete through the middle layers (V peaks at 24% at L23, L at 24% at L20). This reflects the model encoding 'buried aliphatic environment' rather than predicting specific residues. Features at L9 (F9:5728, F9:1281, F9:2619 with projections 57.7, 52.7, 52.4) encode structural context and local sequence patterns consistent with hydrophobic core positions.
perception_phase.context_character: Deeply buried hydrophobic core environment with strong aliphatic character from structural contacts. The local sequence DQQRL[I]FAGKQ places the position between charged residues (D, Q, R, K) but the 3D contacts reveal isolation within a hydrophobic pocket.
key_information_sources: Structural contacts: 8 residues read primarily through L29 attention heads 18 and 7 (structural attention 0.93 and 0.88)
Co-evolutionary signal: 9 coupled positions provide functional constraints, though weaker than structural signal
L9 attention features: F9:5728 (57.7 proj), F9:1281 (52.7 proj) encode hydrophobic core context
L18 attention features: F18:5063 (34.8 proj), F18:7701 (34.4 proj) refine structural environment representation

decision_phase.summary: The decision crystallizes at L24-26 as isoleucine-specific prediction channels activate. L24 MLP neuron N24:5061 writes strongly for I (0.654 proj, with I as top vote). L25 shows the critical transition: I jumps from 9% to 28% as multiple I-specific neurons fire (N25:1243 at 0.472, N25:1779 at 0.453, N25:4948 at 0.411). By L26, I overtakes V permanently. The final layers (L29-33) show massive MLP support: N29:1322 (0.827 proj), N29:4727 (0.784 proj), and especially L32 neurons N32:4433 (1.39 proj) and N32:1797 (0.85 proj) drive I to 99.31%.
decision_phase.transition: The perception-to-decision boundary occurs sharply at L24-25. At L23, the representation still projects most strongly to V (24%) with I at only 9%, reflecting hydrophobic character without commitment. L24 shows first strong I-specific MLP activity (N24:5061 with 0.654 proj), and L25 delivers the decisive shift: both attention (+2.58) and MLP (+2.39) push I upward by 5% total, while V peaks at 29% then begins declining. This is where abstract 'hydrophobic core' representation becomes concrete 'isoleucine' prediction.

candidates.narrative: Isoleucine emerges as the clear winner starting at L26 (28%) and accelerates through the decision phase. L30 SAE features F30:4067 (39.9 proj, attention), F30:6529 (35.6 proj, MLP), and F30:7120 (33.0 proj, MLP) provide strong support. The final push comes from L32-33 MLP neurons: N32:4433 delivers a massive 1.39 projection (top vote for I at 1.39), N32:1797 adds 0.85, and L33 features F33:2789 (156.6 proj), F33:5788 (146.5 proj), F33:3601 (133.0 proj) seal the prediction. I rises from 68% at L29 to 99.31% at L33, reflecting the model's confidence that the branched aliphatic structure of isoleucine optimally fills the buried hydrophobic pocket.
candidates.key_layers: Emerges at L26 (28%), dominant by L29 (68%), final at L33 (99.31%)
key_evidence: N32:4433 (1.39 proj) — strongest single neuron vote for I
F33:2789 (MLP, 156.6 proj) — final-layer I-specific prediction channel
L29 head 18 (+3.3 proj) — structural writer reading hydrophobic contacts

candidates.narrative: Valine is the primary competitor throughout perception and early decision phases, peaking at 29% at L25 before losing to I at L26. V's strength reflects the representation's hydrophobic character: the logit lens projects toward V because the assembled context (buried, aliphatic) is consistent with valine chemistry. However, V lacks the specific prediction channel support that I receives in late layers. While V gets some support from L23 neuron N23:4952 (0.414 proj, with V as top vote at 0.695), it cannot compete with I's massive late-layer backing. V declines steadily after L25, ending at 0.6%.
candidates.key_layers: Strong L4-L25 (peaks 29% at L25), declines L26+ (0.6% final)
key_evidence: N23:4952 (0.414 proj toward I, but 0.695 top vote for V) — V-preferring neuron
Logit lens shows V at 24% at L23, reflecting hydrophobic representation character
Loses decisively to I at L26 when I-specific channels activate

candidates.narrative: Leucine appears prominent in the logit lens through mid-layers (peaks 24% at L20), but this reflects the representation's aliphatic character rather than model belief. L and V are chemically similar to I, so as the model encodes 'buried hydrophobic with branched aliphatic contacts,' the logit lens projects toward all three. L receives modest support from perception-phase neurons (N10:224 gives 0.113 to L, 0.084 to I), but lacks decision-phase prediction channels. Once I-specific features activate at L24+, L collapses to 0.04% by L33.
candidates.key_layers: Prominent L2-L20 (peaks 24% at L20), collapses L24+ (0.04% final)
key_evidence: Peaks at L20 (23.9%) when representation encodes aliphatic core context
N10:224 (0.113 proj to L vs 0.084 to I) — early neuron slightly favoring L
No late-layer prediction channels support L over I

candidates.narrative: Alanine leads the logit lens at L0 (20%) because the initial embedding captures local sequence statistics and A is the smallest hydrophobic residue, serving as a default hydrophobic signal. However, A steadily declines as structural information accumulates, dropping to 13% by L8 and 3% by L23. The representation shifts from 'generic hydrophobic' to 'specific buried aliphatic with branched structure,' which A cannot satisfy. A receives no meaningful decision-phase support and ends at 0.01%.
candidates.key_layers: Leads at L0 (20%), declines steadily through perception phase (0.01% final)
key_evidence: L0 embedding projects 20% to A — reflects local sequence prior
Erased by structural information: drops to 6% by L17 as contacts are read

candidates.narrative: Threonine briefly emerges at L23-24 (peaks 13% at L24), representing a polar alternative hypothesis. This spike occurs at the perception-decision boundary, possibly reflecting uncertainty about whether the position is truly buried or partially exposed. However, T is quickly suppressed by L25-29 MLP neurons that strongly favor hydrophobic residues: N25:3879 erases T with -0.564 proj (top vote for Q at 0.561, not T), and N26:169 erases with -0.426 proj (top vote for T at 0.832, but negative overall). T collapses to 0.03% by L33 as the hydrophobic context dominates.
candidates.key_layers: Brief spike at L24 (13%), suppressed by L29 (0.8%)
key_evidence: Peaks at L24 (12.9%) during perception-decision transition
N25:3879 (-0.564 proj) — eraser neuron suppressing polar alternatives
N26:169 (-0.426 proj) — further suppression of T

turning_points.description: The representation shifts from generic hydrophobic to specific aliphatic character. L18 attention features (F18:5063 at 34.8 proj, F18:7701 at 34.4 proj) refine the structural context. L19 shows strong MLP support for I-compatible chemistry: N19:4014 (0.313 proj, top vote I), N19:2190 (0.276 proj, top vote I), N19:3289 (0.266 proj, top vote I). The logit lens reflects this: L peaks at 24% at L20, then V takes over at L21 as the representation narrows toward branched aliphatics. This is still perception—the model is encoding 'what's here' (buried branched hydrophobic pocket) not yet 'what should go here.'

The decisive perception-to-decision transition. L24 activates first I-specific prediction channels: N24:5061 (0.654 proj, top vote I at 0.654), N24:2042 (0.392 proj, top vote I). L25 delivers the critical shift with both attention (+2.58) and MLP (+2.39) driving I upward by 5% total, while V peaks at 29% then begins irreversible decline. L26 is the crossover: I overtakes V permanently (28% vs 29% becoming I-dominant). This is where abstract hydrophobic representation crystallizes into concrete isoleucine prediction, as neurons with high I-specificity fire decisively.

Final commitment phase with massive MLP amplification. L29-30 show strong I-writing neurons (N29:1322 at 0.827, N29:4727 at 0.784) but also significant erasure (N30:3672 at -0.889, though its top vote is for M at 2.141, suggesting it's suppressing M not I). L32 delivers the knockout: N32:4433 projects 1.39 toward I (largest single neuron contribution), N32:1720 adds 1.086, driving I from 68% at L29 to 96% at L32. L33 features F33:2789 (156.6 proj), F33:5788 (146.5 proj), F33:3601 (133.0 proj) provide final amplification to 99.31%. The model has fully committed to isoleucine as the unique solution to the buried hydrophobic core constraint.

deep_dives.label: Structural attention L29
deep_dives.caption: L29 heads 18 and 7 are the primary structural readers, writing +3.3 and +2.9 toward I with 0.93 and 0.88 structural attention. These heads gather information from the 8 buried hydrophobic contacts that define this position's context.

deep_dives.label: Early SAE features L9
deep_dives.caption: L9 attention features encode the hydrophobic core context being assembled. F9:5728 (57.7 proj), F9:1281 (52.7 proj), and F9:2619 (52.4 proj) represent structural and sequence patterns consistent with buried aliphatic positions.

deep_dives.label: Mid-layer SAE features L18
deep_dives.caption: L18 features refine the structural environment representation. F18:5063 (34.8 proj) and F18:7701 (34.4 proj) encode increasingly specific information about the buried hydrophobic pocket that will ultimately favor isoleucine.

deep_dives.label: Decision onset MLP L24-25
deep_dives.caption: L24-25 neurons mark the perception-to-decision transition. N24:5061 (0.654 proj) and N25:1243 (0.472 proj) are among the first strongly I-specific neurons to fire, initiating the shift from abstract hydrophobic representation to concrete isoleucine prediction.

deep_dives.label: Final commitment MLP L32
deep_dives.caption: L32 neurons deliver the decisive votes. N32:4433 (1.39 proj) provides the single largest contribution to I, with N32:1720 (1.086 proj) and N32:1797 (0.85 proj) adding substantial support. These neurons drive I from 68% to 96%.

deep_dives.label: Final prediction channels L33
deep_dives.caption: L33 MLP features are the final prediction channels. F33:2789 (156.6 proj), F33:5788 (146.5 proj), and F33:3601 (133.0 proj) provide massive amplification, pushing I to 99.31% confidence.

deep_dives.label: Critical velocity event L25
deep_dives.caption: L25 shows the largest coordinated push toward I: attention contributes +2.58, MLP adds +2.39, for a total +4.98 shift. This is the moment when I-specific prediction channels activate decisively, marking the transition from perception to committed prediction.

equation_narrative.resolution: The model correctly predicts isoleucine with 99.31% confidence by assembling a detailed representation of position 44's buried hydrophobic core environment through layers 1-23, then activating isoleucine-specific prediction channels at L24-26. The strongest evidence comes from structural attention at L29 (heads 18 and 7 reading 8 hydrophobic contacts with 0.93 and 0.88 structural attention) combined with massive MLP support in final layers (N32:4433 contributing 1.39 projection, L33 features F33:2789 at 156.6 projection). The model's confidence reflects isoleucine's unique fit: among hydrophobic residues, only I's branched aliphatic structure optimally satisfies the specific geometric and chemical constraints of this deeply buried pocket in ubiquitin's hydrophobic core.
